latestIgtvVideos.title: DIY hair mask for frizzy and dry hair 🌺
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
🌺 After 30 mintiest shampoo your hair and apply conditioner leave it for  5 minutes and then rinse your hair with cold water preferably or last rinse with cold water 

🌺 Apple cider vinegar should be organic @bragglivefoodproducts 

🌺don’t apply on the scalp.
You can apply curd +olive oil + honey on the scalp.
Apple cider vinegar should be diluted hence avoid applying that on the scalp directly.

Honey 🍯 - It adds moisture and shine to even the dullest head of hair.

Yogurt - Aids  growth by stimulating blood circulation,  helps to treat dandruff 

Olive oil - Olive oil moisturizes your hair and reduces scalp irritation, which further reduces dandruff.

Apple Cider Vinegar - It could help strengthen hair and improve luster by lowering hair and scalp pH.It also helps to close or flatten the open cuticles of your hair which in turn leads to frizz.

⁣Tip : it’s better to apply the mask in your bathroom and not in your bedroom 😅

When it comes to self-makeup, I truly believe you learn best when you see it done on the person who’s teaching it—not just on a model.
Doing makeup on yourself is a whole different art—it’s about knowing your own angles, learning your own features, and working with your comfort zone. That’s why I always teach by showing it on myself.

If you’re looking to feel more confident doing your own makeup—stay tuned, more workshops coming soon!
